{"item_id": "df94771dc6:0", "source": "While Materials control the appearance of an object, patterns control the detail by varying the parameters of the material's Bxdf across a surface. This is similar to the way texture artists use textures to control the look of a material. RenderMan ships with a set of patterns that allow texturing, color correction, bumping, and various utility shading systems."}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:1", "source": "The patterns can be divided into the following categories:"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:2", "source": "Image Texture"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:3", "source": "Drive patterns with texture images."}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:4", "source": "PxrMultiTexture"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:5", "source": "PxrProjectionLayer"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:6", "source": "PxrPtexture"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:7", "source": "PxrTexture"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:8", "source": "Procedural Texture"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:9", "source": "Procedurally create noise and patterns."}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:10", "source": "PxrChecker"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:11", "source": "PxrCurvature"}
{"item_id": "df94771dc6:12", "source": "PxrFractal"}
